Alignment and Display in CSS
Text Alignment
text-align: This property controls the horizontal alignment of the text within an element.
left: Aligns the text to the left.
center: Centers the text within the element.
right: Aligns the text to the right.
justify: Justifies the text, aligning it to both the left and right margins.
Vertical Alignment
vertical-align: This property controls the vertical alignment of an element within its parent element.
baseline: Aligns the element's baseline with the baseline of its parent.
top: Aligns the top of the element with the top of its parent.
middle: Centers the element vertically within its parent.
bottom: Aligns the bottom of the element with the bottom of its parent.
Display Property
display: This property controls how an element is displayed.
block: Creates a new block-level element, which takes up the full width of its parent container and starts on a new line.
inline: Creates an inline element, which is displayed in the same line as other inline elements.
inline-block: Creates an inline element that can have a width and height, similar to a block element.
flex: Enables the flexbox layout model for the element and its children.
Example HTML Document:

HTML
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Alignment and Display</title>
  <style>
    .text-container {
      width: 300px;
      border: 1px solid black;
      padding: 10px;
    }

    .text-container p {
      text-align: center;
    }

    .vertical-align-container {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .vertical-align-container img {
      height: 50px;
      margin-right: 10px;
    }

    .display-container {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
    }

    .display-container div {
      border: 1px solid black;
      padding: 10px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h2>Text Alignment</h2>
  <div class="text-container">
    <p>This text is centered.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Vertical Alignment</h2>
  <div class="vertical-align-container">
    <img src="image.jpg" alt="Image">
    <p>This text is vertically aligned with the image.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Display Property</h2>
  <div class="display-container">
    <div>This is a block element.</div>
    <div>This is another block element.</div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>